parameterdescription.para: If one of the expressions is the WHERE clause it needs to be highlighted by its index so that data generated by the expression can know which records need to be sent tot he result providers.

The plan initialized to add the compiled expression into. This is marked as in and out parameter direction because you provide a skeleton plan to be written to, but you cannot provide NULL for this parameter.

briefdescription.para: Recursive function to compile an expression into a plan.

parameterdescription.para: This number is incremented throughout the recursion. When you first call this function the destinationBuffer will be the position of the first buffer allowed to be writen to. You will likely want to set this to 1 so that you keep buffer 0 available. Note that this is not where there final result will be put, it is only the start ID of which buffers can be written to - the function will return an int which is the buffer ID with the real result. You may need to copy that buffer into buffer 0.
The plan the operations will be compiled into.
If this is EagleTrue then a provider will be created for a literal. Otherwise it is assumed the parent will handle the literal.
